00:48:00,183 --> 00:48:01,601
lt is more than that.

444
00:48:01,684 --> 00:48:04,312
More than what?
She was only dancing.

445
00:48:04,395 --> 00:48:07,315
With an American
who is really a Polack.

446
00:48:07,398 --> 00:48:08,983
Says the spic.

447
00:48:11,110 --> 00:48:12,737
You are not so cute.

448
00:48:12,820 --> 00:48:15,281
- That Tony is.
- And he works.

449
00:48:15,365 --> 00:48:16,699
A delivery boy.

450
00:48:16,783 --> 00:48:18,868
- And what are you?
- An assistant.

451
00:48:18,952 --> 00:48:22,121
And Chino makes half
of what the Polack makes.

452
00:48:22,205 --> 00:48:24,249
- The Polack is an American.
- Here comes the whole commercial.

453
00:48:24,332 --> 00:48:26,542
Your mother's a Pole.
Your father's a Swede.

454
00:48:26,626 --> 00:48:28,836
But you were born here.
That's all that you need.

455
00:48:28,920 --> 00:48:31,506
You are an American.
But us?

456
00:48:31,547 --> 00:48:32,882
Foreigners!

457
00:48:32,966 --> 00:48:35,551
Lice. Cockroaches.

458
00:48:35,635 --> 00:48:36,803
But it's true.

459
00:48:36,886 --> 00:48:40,306
When l think about how l thought
it would be for us here.

460
00:48:40,390 --> 00:48:42,809
We came like children,
believing, trusting.

461
00:48:42,850 --> 00:48:44,477
With our hearts open.

462
00:48:44,560 --> 00:48:46,437
With our arms open.

463
00:48:46,479 --> 00:48:49,983
You came with your mouth open.

464
00:48:50,066 --> 00:48:52,026
You did, spic, and you'll
go back in handcuffs.

465
00:48:52,068 --> 00:48:54,070
l'm going back in a Cadillac.

466
00:48:54,153 --> 00:48:55,822
- Air-conditioned.
- Built-in bar.

467
00:48:55,905 --> 00:48:57,615
- Telephone.
- Television.

468
00:48:57,699 --> 00:48:59,200
Compatible color.

469
00:48:59,284 --> 00:49:02,829
lf you had all that here, why would you
want to go back to Puerto Rico?

470
00:49:02,912 --> 00:49:06,332
Even if you didn't have all that here,
why would you want to go back?

471
00:49:06,374 --> 00:49:08,084
lt's so good here?

472
00:49:08,167 --> 00:49:11,421
lt's so good there?
We had nothing.

473
00:49:11,504 --> 00:49:14,841
Ah, we still have nothing,
only more expensive.

474
00:49:16,134 --> 00:49:18,636
Anita Josephina...

475
00:49:18,678 --> 00:49:21,055
- Beatriz del Carmen Margarita.
- lt's plain Anita now.

476
00:49:21,139 --> 00:49:24,601
- Et cetera.
- Leave me alone. At least l--

477
00:49:24,684 --> 00:49:26,936
Once an immigrant,
always an immigrant.

478
00:49:27,020 --> 00:49:30,023
Hey, look, instead of a shampoo,
she's been brainwashed.

479
00:49:30,106 --> 00:49:32,859
- Stop it.
- She's given up Puerto Rico.

480
00:49:32,901 --> 00:49:34,861
Now she's queer for Uncle Sam.

481
00:49:34,903 --> 00:49:38,531
Oh, no. That's not true.

482
00:49:38,573 --> 00:49:41,409
Puerto Rico

483
00:49:41,492 --> 00:49:44,412
My heart's devotion

484
00:49:44,454 --> 00:49:46,623
Let it sink back

485
00:49:46,706 --> 00:49:49,584
ln the ocean

486
00:49:50,835 --> 00:49:55,423
Always the hurricanes blowing

487
00:49:55,506 --> 00:49:58,885
Always the population growing

488
00:50:00,136 --> 00:50:03,056
And the money owing

489
00:50:03,097 --> 00:50:06,017
And the sunlight streaming

490
00:50:06,100 --> 00:50:08,478
And the natives steaming

491
00:50:08,519 --> 00:50:12,523
l like the island Manhattan

492
00:50:12,607 --> 00:50:13,942
l know you do.

493
00:50:13,983 --> 00:50:16,653
Smoke on your pipe

494
00:50:16,694 --> 00:50:18,947
And put that in

