748
01:10:35,035 --> 01:10:37,955
So maybe he decided
to clean up the P.R.s instead.

749
01:10:41,917 --> 01:10:44,670
- Doc, you ain't gonna close up now?
- l'm not?

750
01:10:44,753 --> 01:10:47,381
- Listen, we got a war council here.
- A who?

751
01:10:47,464 --> 01:10:50,509
- To determine weapons.
- We gonna set up a mix with the P.R.s.

752
01:10:50,550 --> 01:10:53,637
Weapons.
You couldn't play basketball?

753
01:10:53,762 --> 01:10:55,097
Get with it, buster.

754
01:10:55,078 --> 01:10:58,331
You don't understand.
We got special business comin' here.

755
01:10:58,414 --> 01:11:01,876
- Makin' trouble for the Puerto Ricans?
- They make trouble for us.

756
01:11:01,918 --> 01:11:04,128
For you, trouble is a relief.

757
01:11:04,212 --> 01:11:06,714
We gotta stand up to 'em.
lt's important.

758
01:11:06,756 --> 01:11:09,842
Fightin' over a little piece
of street is so important?

759
01:11:09,884 --> 01:11:12,220
- To us it is.
- To hoodlums it is.

760
01:11:12,303 --> 01:11:14,222
- Who you callin' hoodlums?
- War councils--

761
01:11:14,305 --> 01:11:16,683
- Don't start, Doc.
- When l was your age--

762
01:11:16,724 --> 01:11:18,184
When you was my age?

763
01:11:18,267 --> 01:11:21,688
When my old man was my age--
my brother was my age.

764
01:11:21,771 --> 01:11:24,023
You was never my age,
none of ya.

765
01:11:24,107 --> 01:11:27,402
And the sooner you creeps get hip
to that, the sooner you'll dig us!

766
01:11:27,485 --> 01:11:30,279
l'll dig you an early grave,
that's what l'll dig.

767
01:11:30,321 --> 01:11:31,990
Dig, dig, dig.

768
01:12:15,742 --> 01:12:18,202
Okay, Doc, set 'em up.
Cokes all around.

769
01:12:18,286 --> 01:12:20,204
Let's get down to business.

770
01:12:20,288 --> 01:12:23,082
Bernardo hasn't learned
the procedures of gracious livin'.

771
01:12:23,166 --> 01:12:26,419
l don't like you either,
so cut it.

772
01:12:26,502 --> 01:12:29,005
- Kick it, Doc.
- Boys, couldn't you maybe talk--

773
01:12:29,088 --> 01:12:30,798
Kick it!

774
01:12:46,314 --> 01:12:48,316
We challenge you to a rumble.

775
01:12:48,358 --> 01:12:50,985
All out, once and for all.
Accept?

776
01:12:51,069 --> 01:12:54,364
- On what terms?
- Whatever terms you're callin'.

777
01:12:54,447 --> 01:12:56,783
You crossed the line
once too often.

778
01:12:56,866 --> 01:12:59,452
- You started it.
- Who jumped Baby John this afternoon?

779
01:12:59,535 --> 01:13:02,538
- Who jumped me first day l moved here?
- Who asked you to move here?

780
01:13:02,622 --> 01:13:04,582
- Move where you're wanted!
- Spics!

781
01:13:04,624 --> 01:13:06,250
- Mick!
- Wop!

782
01:13:14,342 --> 01:13:15,593
We accept.

783
01:13:17,095 --> 01:13:19,305
- Time.
- Tomorrow?

784
01:13:19,389 --> 01:13:21,599
After dark.

785
01:13:24,352 --> 01:13:26,312
- Place.
- The park?

786
01:13:29,023 --> 01:13:29,983
The river.

787
01:13:34,862 --> 01:13:36,280
Under the highway.

788
01:13:40,034 --> 01:13:42,078
- Weapons.
- Hey, Doc!

789
01:13:44,330 --> 01:13:45,248
Weapons.

790
01:13:50,920 --> 01:13:53,298
- You call.
- Your challenge.

791
01:13:54,465 --> 01:13:56,384
Afraid to call?

792
01:14:00,263 --> 01:14:02,015
Rocks.

793
01:14:02,098 --> 01:14:04,309
- Belts.
- Pipes.

794
01:14:04,350 --> 01:14:06,436
- Cans.
- Bricks.

795
01:14:06,519 --> 01:14:07,687
- Bats!
- Clubs!

796
01:14:07,770 --> 01:14:10,606
- Chains!
- Bottles, knives, guns!

797
01:14:10,690 --> 01:14:14,027
- What a coop full of chickens.
- Who you callin' chicken?

798
01:14:14,110 --> 01:14:16,821
- Every dog knows his own.
- l'm callin' you all chicken.

799
01:14:16,863 --> 01:14:19,532
Big tough buddy boys
gotta throw bricks, huh?

800
01:14:19,615 --> 01:14:22,035
Afraid to get in close?
Afraid to slug it out?

801
01:14:22,076 --> 01:14:24,662
- Afraid to use plain skin?
- Not even garbage?

802
01:14:24,704 --> 01:14:26,497
- That ain't a rumble.
- Who says?

803
01:14:26,581 --> 01:14:30,251
- You said call weapons.
- lt can be clinched by a fair fight.

804
01:14:30,335 --> 01:14:34,130
lf you've got the guts to risk that.
Best man from each gang to slug it out.

805
01:14:36,591 --> 01:14:40,345
l would enjoy to risk that.
Okay, fair fight.

806
01:14:40,428 --> 01:14:43,556
Wait a minute.
The commanders say yes or no.

807
01:14:45,725 --> 01:14:47,018
Fair fight.

808
01:14:49,812 --> 01:14:51,814
When l get through with you...

809
01:14:51,898 --> 01:14:54,233
you will be like a fish
after skinning.

810
01:14:54,317 --> 01:14:56,944
Your best man
fights our best man...

811
01:14:57,028 --> 01:14:59,697
and we pick him.

812
01:15:01,157 --> 01:15:03,076
- l thought l would be fighting--
- You shook on it.

813
01:15:07,372 --> 01:15:09,332
Yes, l shook on it.

814
01:15:09,374 --> 01:15:12,001
lf you wanna change your mind,
we can still--

815
01:15:22,345 --> 01:15:25,640
- Bernardo, would you like a cigarette?
- No, thank you. l don't smoke.

816
01:15:30,561 --> 01:15:32,814
Evening, Lieutenant.

817
01:15:32,897 --> 01:15:35,108
l and Tony was just closin' up.

818
01:15:36,609 --> 01:15:40,780
Well, now,
this is more like it, fellas.

819
01:15:40,863 --> 01:15:43,241
Warms me all over
to see you this way.

820
01:15:43,324 --> 01:15:46,911
And after only a couple of words from me
at the playground this afternoon.

821
01:15:46,995 --> 01:15:48,788
Oh, do you mind?

822
01:15:48,871 --> 01:15:52,041
l have no mind.
l'm the village idiot.

823
01:15:53,209 --> 01:15:56,462
Headquarters hears about this,
l may even get a promotion.

824
01:15:57,672 --> 01:15:59,799
Good deal all around,
huh, Bernardo?

825
01:16:00,967 --> 01:16:02,927
l get a promotion...

826
01:16:02,969 --> 01:16:06,306
and you Puerto Ricans
get what you've been itchin' for.

827
01:16:06,347 --> 01:16:08,891
Use of the playground,
use of the gym...

828
01:16:08,933 --> 01:16:12,395
the streets, the candy store.

829
01:16:12,478 --> 01:16:16,399
So what if they do turn this whole town
into a stinkin' pigsty?

830
01:16:16,441 --> 01:16:18,526
Don't stop him.
He wants to get home...

831
01:16:18,609 --> 01:16:21,487
write letters to San Juan,
tell 'em how he's got it made here.

832
01:16:23,281 --> 01:16:27,243
What l mean is, clear out!
l said, clear out!

833
01:16:30,788 --> 01:16:33,166
Oh, yeah, sure, l know.

834
01:16:33,249 --> 01:16:36,544
lt's a free country
and l ain't got the right.

835
01:16:36,628 --> 01:16:38,963
But l got a badge.

836
01:16:39,047 --> 01:16:41,174
What do you got?

837
01:16:41,257 --> 01:16:43,926
Things are tough all over.
Beat it!

838
01:17:16,167 --> 01:17:18,086
Okay, fellas.

839
01:17:19,295 --> 01:17:21,422
Where's the rumble gonna be?

840
01:17:23,049 --> 01:17:26,469
Come on. l know regular Americans
don't rub with the gold-teeth unless--

841
01:17:26,552 --> 01:17:29,013
- Look, Lieutenant--
- You shut your mouth!

842
01:17:32,308 --> 01:17:34,394
Come on, Baby John...

843
01:17:34,477 --> 01:17:37,647
before that smooth little kisser
of yours gets cut up for life.

844
01:17:37,689 --> 01:17:39,399
Now, where's it gonna be?

845
01:17:40,108 --> 01:17:41,609
The river?

846
01:17:41,693 --> 01:17:43,528
The park?

847
01:17:47,198 --> 01:17:49,575
Look, fellas, l'm for you.

848
01:17:49,659 --> 01:17:52,745
l want this beat cleaned up,
and you can do it for me.

849
01:17:52,829 --> 01:17:55,248
l'll even lend a hand
if things get rough.

850
01:17:55,331 --> 01:17:57,417
Now, where ya gonna rumble?

851
01:18:00,253 --> 01:18:02,171
The playground?

852
01:18:03,965 --> 01:18:06,092
Sweeney's lot?

853
01:18:12,015 --> 01:18:15,226
Why don't you get smart,
you stupid hooligans?

854
01:18:15,310 --> 01:18:18,146
l oughta take you to the station
and throw you in the can right now.

855
01:18:18,187 --> 01:18:21,149
You and the tinhorn
immigrant scum you come from!

856
01:18:23,901 --> 01:18:26,195
How's your old man's d.t.'s, A-rab?

857
01:18:28,865 --> 01:18:30,825
How's the action on your
mother's side of the street, Action?

858
01:18:33,536 --> 01:18:35,830
One of these days
there won't be anybody to hold ya.

859
01:18:35,872 --> 01:18:38,124
Get him outta here!
Come on!

860
01:18:39,626 --> 01:18:42,170
Don't worry, l'll find out
where it's gonna be.

861
01:18:42,253 --> 01:18:46,549
So be sure to finish each other off,
because if you don't, l will!

862
01:18:55,975 --> 01:18:57,935
Oh, yeah, sure.

863
01:18:57,977 --> 01:18:59,771
Understand 'em.

864
01:18:59,854 --> 01:19:03,483
That's what they keep tellin' me
down at headquarters: understand.

865
01:19:03,566 --> 01:19:07,278
Well, you try keeping hoodlums in line
and see what it does to you.

866
01:19:11,366 --> 01:19:14,786
lt wouldn't give me
a mouth like his.

867
01:19:18,373 --> 01:19:21,876
Come on, Doc.
Don't let it get ya.

868
01:19:21,960 --> 01:19:23,628
l'm sick.

869
01:19:23,711 --> 01:19:25,880
You heard.
lt's gonna be a fair fight.

870
01:19:25,964 --> 01:19:27,882
And that's gonna cure somethin'?

871
01:19:27,966 --> 01:19:32,387
From here on in,
everything's gonna be all right.

872
01:19:32,470 --> 01:19:34,889
- l got a feelin'.
- What have you been takin' tonight?

873
01:19:34,973 --> 01:19:36,766
A trip to the moon.

874
01:19:36,849 --> 01:19:40,395
And l'll tell ya a secret, Doc.
lt ain't a man that's up there.

875
01:19:40,478 --> 01:19:42,772
lt's a girl.

876
01:19:42,814 --> 01:19:44,899
A lady.

877
01:19:51,823 --> 01:19:54,075
So that's why you
made it a fair fight.

878
01:19:54,158 --> 01:19:56,119
l'm gonna see her tomorrow
and l can't wait.

879
01:19:58,121 --> 01:20:01,291
- Things aren't tough enough?
- Doc, l'm in love.

880
01:20:01,374 --> 01:20:04,127
- And you're not frightened?
- Should l be?

881
01:20:07,422 --> 01:20:10,383
No, l'm frightened enough
for the both of you.

882
01:22:43,028 --> 01:22:45,197
What has Chino done to her?

883
01:22:45,280 --> 01:22:47,449
Chino? Why Chino?

884
01:22:47,532 --> 01:22:49,826
Maybe she's just
dolling up for us.

885
01:22:51,703 --> 01:22:53,497
Rosalia, Consuelo...

886
01:22:53,538 --> 01:22:56,416
my adorable friends,
can you keep a secret?

887
01:22:56,458 --> 01:22:58,418
l'm hot for secrets.

888
01:23:00,087 --> 01:23:02,547
No, l won't tell you.

889
01:23:02,631 --> 01:23:04,091
- What?
- What?

890
01:23:04,132 --> 01:23:07,678
- The poor girl is out of her mind.
- l am-- crazy.

891
01:23:07,761 --> 01:23:11,139
She might be at that.
She looks somehow different.

892
01:23:11,139 --> 01:23:13,975
- l do?
- And l think she is up to something.

893
01:23:14,059 --> 01:23:15,519
l am?

894
01:23:15,602 --> 01:23:18,313
''l do?'' ''l am?''
She talks like a parrot.

895
01:23:18,397 --> 01:23:20,816
What is going on with you, Maria?

896
01:23:20,857 --> 01:23:23,860
l feel pretty
Oh, so pretty

897
01:23:23,902 --> 01:23:27,030
l feel pretty and witty and gay

898
01:23:27,114 --> 01:23:31,326
And l pity any girl
who isn't me today

899
01:23:33,453 --> 01:23:36,456
l feel charming
Oh, so charming

900
01:23:36,540 --> 01:23:39,668
lt's alarming how charming l feel

901
01:23:39,710 --> 01:23:44,089
And so pretty
That l hardly can believe l'm real

902
01:23:46,800 --> 01:23:49,970
See the pretty girl
in that mirror there

903
01:23:50,012 --> 01:23:53,098
Who can that attractive girl be

904
01:23:53,181 --> 01:23:54,766
Such a pretty face
Such a pretty dress

905
01:23:54,850 --> 01:23:57,102
Such a pretty smile
Such a pretty me

906
01:23:58,603 --> 01:24:01,606
l feel stunning
and entrancing

907
01:24:01,690 --> 01:24:04,860
Feel like running
and dancing for joy

908
01:24:04,943 --> 01:24:10,157
For l'm loved
by a pretty wonderful boy

909
01:24:14,828 --> 01:24:17,998
Have you met my good friend Maria

910
01:24:18,081 --> 01:24:21,251
The craziest girl on the block

911
01:24:21,335 --> 01:24:24,046
You'll know her
the minute you see her

912
01:24:24,129 --> 01:24:27,591
She's the one who is in
an advanced state of shock

913
01:24:27,674 --> 01:24:30,635
She thinks she's in love
She thinks she's in Spain

914
01:24:31,678 --> 01:24:34,890
She isn't in love
She's merely insane

915
01:24:35,682 --> 01:24:39,728
lt must be the heat
or some rare disease

916
01:24:39,811 --> 01:24:43,273
Or too much to eat
Or maybe it's fleas

917
01:24:44,149 --> 01:24:47,527
Keep away from her
Send for Chino

918
01:24:47,569 --> 01:24:50,572
This is not the Maria we know

919
01:24:50,656 --> 01:24:54,201
Modest and pure
polite and refined

920
01:24:54,284 --> 01:24:57,621
Well-bred and mature
and out of her mind

921
01:24:59,289 --> 01:25:01,166
Miss America!

922
01:25:03,460 --> 01:25:05,837
Miss America!
Bravo! Speech!

923
01:25:07,756 --> 01:25:10,842
l feel pretty
Oh, so pretty

924
01:25:10,926 --> 01:25:14,054
That the city
should give me its key

925
01:25:14,137 --> 01:25:18,141
A committee should be organized
to honor me

926
01:25:20,602 --> 01:25:23,647
l feel dizzy
l feel sunny

927
01:25:23,730 --> 01:25:26,942
l feel fizzy and funny and fine

928
01:25:26,983 --> 01:25:31,446
And so pretty
Miss America can just resign

929
01:25:34,199 --> 01:25:36,410
See the pretty girl
in that mirror there

930
01:25:36,451 --> 01:25:39,579
- What mirror where
- Who can that attractive girl be

931
01:25:39,663 --> 01:25:41,581
- Which, what, where, who
- Such a pretty face

932
01:25:41,665 --> 01:25:44,876
Such a pretty dress, such a pretty smile
Such a pretty me

933
01:25:46,461 --> 01:25:48,088
l feel stunning

934
01:25:48,130 --> 01:25:49,881
And entrancing

935
01:25:49,965 --> 01:25:52,801
Feel like running
and dancing for joy

936
01:25:52,884 --> 01:25:58,223
For l'm loved
by a pretty wonderful boy

937
01:26:07,065 --> 01:26:10,777
You want to sing, do it with needles,
or you'll be singing for your supper.

938
01:26:10,861 --> 01:26:14,448
But Madam Lucia, what can you expect?
We use Singer sewing machines.

939
01:26:14,531 --> 01:26:17,993
Sure. You make the bad joke home
where l can't hear it!

940
01:26:18,076 --> 01:26:21,121
Well, go now.
lt's closing time. Shoo!

941
01:26:24,333 --> 01:26:26,335
You pull down the shades,
pick up the pins...

942
01:26:26,376 --> 01:26:28,795
turn off the lights
and lock the doors.

943
01:26:34,301 --> 01:26:36,595
Oh, the jail is opened.

944
01:26:36,636 --> 01:26:38,597
l thought she'd never leave.

945
01:26:38,638 --> 01:26:42,642
lt's hard to believe that old bag
was once a young bag like us.

946
01:26:42,726 --> 01:26:45,520
Let's go before she
changes her mind and comes back.

947
01:26:45,604 --> 01:26:48,565
You go, querida.
l will lock up.

948
01:26:48,648 --> 01:26:50,901
- Why?
- l have work.

949
01:26:50,901 --> 01:26:54,154
- Do it tomorrow.
- l am in no hurry.

950
01:26:54,237 --> 01:26:58,992
l am. l'm going home now
and take a nice long bubble bath.

951
01:26:59,076 --> 01:27:00,369
Black Orchid.

952
01:27:03,205 --> 01:27:06,667
All over. l got a date with Nardo
after the rumble.

953
01:27:07,668 --> 01:27:08,960
What rumble?

954
01:27:10,462 --> 01:27:13,965
Oh, well, Nardo's Sharks
and those boys at the dance.

955
01:27:15,092 --> 01:27:17,386
They fight each other tonight?

956
01:27:17,469 --> 01:27:19,388
They don't play potsy.

957
01:27:21,682 --> 01:27:23,975
Why must they always fight?

958
01:27:24,059 --> 01:27:28,021
Well, you saw how they dance-- like
they gotta get rid of something quick.

959
01:27:28,105 --> 01:27:29,523
That's how they fight.

960
01:27:29,564 --> 01:27:32,317
To get rid of what?

961
01:27:32,401 --> 01:27:36,113
Too much feeling.
And they do get rid of it.

962
01:27:36,196 --> 01:27:40,409
Boy, after a fight,
that brother of yours is so healthy.

963
01:27:40,492 --> 01:27:43,161
Definitely: Black Orchid.

964
01:27:57,092 --> 01:28:00,137
''You go, querida.
l will lock up.''

965
01:28:03,432 --> 01:28:06,351
lt's too early for noches.
Buenas tardes.

966
01:28:11,398 --> 01:28:14,651
He just came from the drugstore
to deliver aspirin.

967
01:28:14,735 --> 01:28:17,821
- You'll need it.
- Not us.

968
01:28:17,863 --> 01:28:20,240
We're fine.
We're out of the world.

969
01:28:20,282 --> 01:28:22,534
You're out of your heads.

970
01:28:22,617 --> 01:28:26,705
- We're 12 feet in the air.
- Anita can see that.

971
01:28:31,335 --> 01:28:33,503
You will not tell?

972
01:28:36,631 --> 01:28:40,594
Tell what? How can l know
what goes on 12 feet over my head?

973
01:28:42,637 --> 01:28:46,058
You better be home in 15 minutes.

974
01:28:54,691 --> 01:28:57,527
lt's all right.
She likes us.

975
01:28:57,611 --> 01:29:00,155
But she is worried,
and so am l.

976
01:29:00,238 --> 01:29:03,325
- That's foolish.
- Are you going to that rumble tonight?

977
01:29:05,619 --> 01:29:08,121
- Why?
- You must go and stop it.

978
01:29:08,205 --> 01:29:11,708
l have stopped it. lt's only gonna be
a fistfight now between two of 'em.

979
01:29:11,792 --> 01:29:14,127
Any fight is no good for us.

980
01:29:14,211 --> 01:29:16,129
Everything is good for us.
We got magic.

981
01:29:16,213 --> 01:29:19,216
Listen, and hear me.

982
01:29:19,299 --> 01:29:20,926
You must go and stop it.

983
01:29:22,552 --> 01:29:24,471
lt means that much to you?

984
01:29:26,056 --> 01:29:27,516
l will, then.

985
01:29:28,725 --> 01:29:32,145
l believe you.
You do have magic.

986
01:29:32,229 --> 01:29:33,730
Of course.

987
01:29:34,815 --> 01:29:37,192
l've got you.

